# Cursor Core Rules

Follow `AGENTS.md` as primary guidance for:

- project context
- engineering rules
- safety rules
- verification checklist
- MCP governance
- documentation contract (§7 — Obsidian vault)

When `AGENTS.md` and this file conflict, prioritize `AGENTS.md`.

## Documentation vault (same as `CLAUDE.md` / Claude Code)

Treat **`docs/vault/`** as the live product and architecture source of truth (Obsidian-compatible markdown).

**At the start of any substantive task** (feature, bugfix, refactor, API change), read:

1. `docs/vault/README.md` — MOC: where ADR, runbooks, entities, archive plans live.
2. `docs/vault/product/status.md` — recent changes, priorities, dashboard §7 pointers.

**While implementing**, use `docs/vault/architecture/code-map.md` to jump to the right code paths.

**When changing a product or architecture decision**, add or update an ADR under `docs/vault/adr/` when practical.

**Before considering work done**, if behavior or contracts changed, update `docs/vault/product/status.md` (section «Последние изменения») and any affected vault architecture notes — same expectation as for Claude Code.

**Do not** use `docs/archive/*-monolith-*.md` or `docs/archive/vault-plans-*` as the authoritative spec for new work; they are history only (see `AGENTS.md` §7).
